.TH PODLINER 1 "2025-11-18" "podliner 1.1.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podliner \- terminal podcast player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podliner
[\-h|\-\-help] [\-V|\-\-version]
[\-\-engine ENGINE]
[\-\-theme THEME]
[\-\-feed URL]
[\-\-search QUERY]
[\-\-opml\-import FILE [\-\-import\-mode MODE]]
[\-\-opml\-export FILE]
[\-\-offline]
[\-\-ascii]
[\-\-log\-level LEVEL]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B podliner
is a cross\-platform terminal podcast player. It supports local/remote playback, a download queue, OPML import/export, and a keyboard\-driven TUI.

In the TUI, press
.B :
to open the command palette. Type
.B :help
to see commands, keys, and engine capabilities.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-engine ENGINE
Preferred audio engine. Canonical values:
.B auto
|
.B vlc
|
.B mpv
|
.B ffplay
|
.B mediafoundation
(Windows only).
.TP
.B \-\-theme THEME
UI theme. Common values:
.B base
|
.B accent
(menu accent)
|
.B native
|
.B auto .
.TP
.B \-\-feed URL
Preselect a feed at startup.
.TP
.B \-\-search QUERY
Apply a search filter at startup.
.TP
.B \-\-opml\-import FILE
Import feeds from OPML. Use with
.B \-\-import\-mode
.
.TP
.B \-\-import\-mode MODE
OPML import behavior:
.B add
(append) or
.B replace
(clear and import).
.TP
.B \-\-opml\-export FILE
Export current feeds to OPML.
.TP
.B \-\-offline
Start in offline mode (no network fetches).
.TP
.B \-\-ascii
Force ASCII glyphs (disable Unicode box drawing).
.TP
.B \-\-log\-level LEVEL
Logging level:
.B debug
|
.B info
|
.B warn
|
.B error .
.SH COMMANDS (IN TUI)
Type
.B :
then a command. Examples:
.PP
.B :refresh
(update feeds),
.B :downloads
(show queue),
.B :engine mpv
(switch engine),
.B :q
(quit).
Run
.B :help
for the full catalog.
.SH FILES
Podliner follows XDG directories.
.TP
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/podliner/appsettings.json
User preferences (theme, layout, UI options).
.TP
.B $XDG_DATA_HOME/podliner/library/library.json
Library (feeds, episodes, queue, history).
.TP
.B $XDG_DATA_HOME/podliner/downloads/
Downloaded audio files (outside the library database).
.PP
If variables are unset, defaults are
.B ~/.config
and
.B ~/.local/share
respectively.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PODLINER_GLYPHS
Set to
.B ascii
to force ASCII glyphs.
.TP
.B http_proxy, https_proxy, no_proxy
Standard proxy variables honored by HTTP requests.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success; non\-zero on failure.
